---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How we review · ToolVerdict"
  description="ToolVerdict's review methodology: how we buy, test, score, and publish verdicts on SaaS and AI tools — and what we will never do."
  path="/about/"
>
  <section class="container about">
    <span class="mono-tag">About</span>
    <h1 class="about-title">We review tools the way you'd want someone to review yours.</h1>
    <p class="about-lede">
      ToolVerdict exists because most "reviews" are press releases with affiliate links. Ours are
      test reports.
    </p>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What we actually do</h2>
      <p>
        Every tool we cover is purchased with our own money, at the plan tier a real buyer would
        choose. We then run it through a fixed brief — the same tasks, documents, and deadlines we
        give every competitor in the same comparison. Vendor demo accounts and guided tours don't
        count as testing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Scores are decided before publication and are not negotiable afterward. When a tool
        changes — a price hike, a new feature, a regression — the article gets a dated update, not
        a silent rewrite.
      </p>

      <h2>How scoring works</h2>
      <p>
        Every verdict uses the same four weighted criteria: <strong>output quality</strong> (does
        it actually do the job?), <strong>speed and friction</strong> (how fast from signup to
        useful result?), <strong>pricing honesty</strong> (are the advertised prices the real
        prices?), and <strong>learning curve</strong> (can a normal human run it without a
        certification?).
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        cols={['Score band', 'What it means', 'Typical example']}
        rows={[
          ['9.0 – 10', 'Exceptional. Buy it now; the flaws are footnotes.', 'Category leader with honest pricing'],
          ['7.5 – 8.9', 'Strong. Right choice for most buyers, with known caveats.', 'Great core, weak mobile app'],
          ['6.0 – 7.4', 'Situational. Good for a specific use case, not a general one.', 'Powerful but hostile onboarding'],
          ['Below 6.0', 'Not recommended at current price. We publish these too.', 'Oversold features, surprise fees'],
        ]}
        caption="The ToolVerdict score bands"
      />

      <h2>What we will never do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Accept payment for placement, score, or removal of a negative verdict.</li>
        <li>Review a tool using only a vendor-provided sandbox or guided demo.</li>
        <li>Publish a comparison where the comparison table was written by one of the vendors.</li>
        <li>Hide affiliate relationships — they are disclosed in the footer and in each article.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        Got a price change, a dead feature, or a factual error? Send it to us via the <a
          href="/contact/">contact page</a
        > with a source. Verified corrections are applied within 48 hours and logged in the
        article.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding-block: 2.5rem 2rem;
  }
  .about-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.6vw, 3.1rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .about-lede {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 58ch;
  }
  .about .prose {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
